The São Tomé and Príncipe authorities have introduced a number of precautionary measures in response to the coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic.
From 19 March, the São Tomé and Príncipe authorities have prohibited the entry of all foreign travellers into the country for 15 days. Nationals of São Tomé and Príncipe and foreign residents in the country will be subject to obligatory quarantine in their homes on return. Charter flights and cruise ships are similarly prohibited.
For information on how to return to the UK from São Tomé and Príncipe, see Return to the UK.
